rComments: There were a lot of students who complained about her disorganized character and inconsistency with handouts. But in fact, she accommodated students with a lot of things! In her class, you DO need attend the class, DO the homework, and DO study!! Pretty simple, but a lot of students expect too much for little effort that they put into. DO THE WORK.

Lovely person but disorganized. Isn't clear; may mention midterm and final and marks here and there but does not tell you crucial information unless you ask numerous times. Felt left in the dark throughout. Content is just written out of the book and exercises are from the book. Midterm, assignments and final are very easy if you learn it.

She is a very kind lady, she is incredibly disorganized and confusing. I managed to pull through with previous french knowledge, but she barely teaches. Half way through the semester, people just stop showing up because she teaches so poorly. There are weekly homework which is easy marks, the midterm and the exam is easy. You just need 2 kno enough
She is not helpful at all. All she does is read the textbook to you. I did not learn anything in this class. She is very easy when marking so you can get a good mark.

Very nice lady but she is so unclear, she does not explain anything. She does not do an intro to the class, just starts writing things on the board for you to copy down. She speaks in French to people who are trying to learn French. I only understand 15% of what she says. I am an A student in every other class.

Terrible Prof, She would start teaching when there were only about 5 people in the class, didn't teach me anything i didn't know. Only taught directly from the text book or sheets printed from online websites. She corrects you before your done writing the answer on the board, and she doesn't explain things clearly. Overall I don't recommend her.
Terrible class - teacher did not explain material while teaching and assumed students had enough knowledge on their own. Would not recommend for any future students.. sorry
SHE IS THE BEST! I took 1510 with her and 1511 with her and her way of teaching is simply the best! If you work hard and try to understand everything, you will be rewarded well.

She is a very nice lady. HOWEVER, she should not be teaching. She is teaching a language to a group of students with little comprehension of the language and she does not explain a single thing. There isn't even any clarity or direction to her teaching. she shows up and without barely any introduction she starts doing excersizes out of the textbook
